caption: The menu and service were ahead of my expectations. I really loved the ambience of this restaurant. First-rate restaurant to take the family out for lunch.
Definitely a place worth trying, the food is awesome and well prepared, the prices are convenient and it is always well kept here. Fantastic work.
Delicious!

One of my favorite spots to eat in the area. Super fresh ingredients, decent prices for great quality meat, the broth is 🔥, and I also just had the green tea ice cream and highly recommend it. Darryl and his team are all great too. 10/10
Awesome service and delicious food! My family and I had a great experience and can't wait to go back.
I tried this place in the past with my friend and I am addicted ever since. I enjoyed the fantastic vibes and tasty dishes and drinks. 5 stars from me.

We like a lot hanging out. Last night we  visited this excellent place which we didn’t know before. We passed a delightful time there with exceptional food and a nice team and a talented chief cook. Always a fun time! Great staff and owner!
This spot is worth giving a shot. They have big portions for reasonable prices. Regularly clean and with fantastic ambience. Will come visit again.
Always such a great experience. Great staff

First date out of quarantine, and a wonderful experience!  Very relaxed.   Everything was immaculately clean!   And the food of course, spot on as always!   Thank you guys for making our first trip out great!   Looking forward to the next time.
Would definitely recommend visiting this place. Fantastic character, delicious food, fantastic customer service. Highly recommended.

This place is my favorite. I visit plenty of restaurants but here I go the most. The team is very welcoming and the food they serve is so good. I never miss an opportunity to have a decent dinner in this restaurant. I highly recommend this place.

First time for shabu. This place us amazing! Friendly, fast and excellent food. Will go back
Favorite place! Great food & price!
The food is regularly fresh and flavorful, employees hands over awesome customer service. I love how clean it is and atmosphere. Will visit here again.

Great service and food!
This spot has awesome service as well as tasty meals. My favourite restaurant ever. The food arrived quick and the rates were affordable. Recommended.
The service is constantly prompt, awesome vibes, nice employees. Will return here again when I arrive in the area.
My favorite hot pot restaurant.  Service is fast and food is great! I always  recommend family and friends here.
Great people. Great service. Great food

My family and I love this plac! Have been coming here for years and have tried other places that are closer, but choose to keep coming back here. The beef is aleays super tender and fresh and vegetables always on point.
I always come by purchasing some food in this place. I enjoy the speedy customer service and well cooked dishes. Great work.
The absolute best. Their peanut sauce is the best
Had a good experience here with my daughter. The food arrives fast and the customer service is just good. Prices are convenient.
Food is great, decent prices for how much food you get. Staff has been super nice every time I have gone.  Also, they have forks.
Great food and pretty good service
AMAZING FOOD AND SERVICE

Stopped by here after our reservations for teppanyaki in Huntington Beach fell through due to poor service, and we were not disappointed. The soups are very flavorful and come with plenty of noodles and veggies to make it to your liking …

Very Good! Delicious. Spicy miso broth was very good and spicy. Be careful how long this simmers or it will be salty at the end. Tempura Vegetables were tasty. Price is a little high, but fair amount of veggies and thin sliced meats. Lamb, short rib and beef are good choices. Pork is too tough unless you pull very quick.,
It's a good place to go out and have a great meal. I tried the spice miso broth and it was delicious.
Excellent Shabu...ordered meat lovers that allows you to have more meat instead of having soup and veges later... Awesome!!!

CAB brisket is relatively cheap and filling. Unlimited veggies sauces is great and the sauces are pretty tasty but nothing out of the ordinary. The service is great, it was very clean and wasn't too crowded. definitely worth a shot if you've tried a lot of the other shabu places and are looking to try something new.
Fabulous Japanese Hot Pot
Best shabu I've ever had. Very good service especially Dalena. He is always good quality and the sauce is consistently tasty. 10 out of 10 would recommend.
Clean location with good service and options. Looks like the happy hour is legit too. Be ready to cook, be a bit warm, be hungry and be in close quarters and you should have a great time

We tried their cheapest tier of meat, certified angus beef. Meat quality was superb and tender, always wished there were some chewing needed. I got their spicy miso and broth was flavorful, not too overwhelming. The vegetable seemed fresh …

The menu system is not very intuitive, although you can upgrade later. Honestly it's SO expensive. $$ is not even close. You'll end up spending $60 on SOUP for two to get full. It was good but honestly I forgot all about it. I think the minimum soup cost was $17!!! You could get so much pho instead.
Good food and friendly service
Good food and good service
Great food!
Great food friendly service  nice clean restaurant prices are very good lots of parking

Probably one of the best shabu spots in the area. There is sometimes a wait but the waiters will seat you immediately. Good service and the meat is less fatty for the price you pay compared to other spots.

First time in the resturant. It was clean and the staff was courteous. The menu had plenty of options to choose from along with other amenities. After you pick what you want you are served a big pot of broth that you choose then you let it …
Fresh food, lots of option on the meat and seafood. Broth was good, friendly staff. A little bit pricey.
Love their interior decorations and set up. Service was awesome plus good food. They got good deal on happy hour!!!
Rip off prices and broken bowl. Never shabu here.
I love this place!
Great food and the servers were excellent. Always enjoy eating here!
Best Shabu place I've been to. The food is always good and the service is even better. They are very accommodating.  We always have a great experience. Highly recommend this place.
Great servers and atmosphere. The food is delicious!
We go here at least once a month
One of our favorite restaurants. Great quality meat and delicious sauces. Always great service.
Good food

It was our first time there and we loved it.  The waiter was very friendly and took the time to explain everything.  You cook your own food in a broth of your choosing.  Since it was our first time at a restaurant like this I would compare it to fondue with a broth.  We'll be back.
Service was pretty bad.
I didn't realize each bowl had a separator so both people didn't have to order the same broth but still share the same heating element/table.

Delicious shabu shabu with excellent service. Good quality meats bit a little bit pricey as these types of places can be. I highly suggest the spicy miso broth over the regular seaweed one. Comfortable and clean.
Shinobu Shabu is fantastic. Delicious cuts of meats with many different options. Friendly and prompt service.

I used to go to Sakura Shabu and it was great then they changed to Slice Shabu and they started to nickle and dime the customer and the Shabu is getting bad. I am glad I found this place and really enjoyed the friendly service and good Shabu. Definitely recommend this place.
The place and the workers are awesome. Food is great too!!
Our spot, great choice for brunches
Great place to eat Shabu I really like it every week me and my wife we always come back to eat at this place
Fun place to take friends.
The food here is great.
The food is real great here.
Always good!
Amazing service and food was great! Must stop by when in the area.

I try to eat Shabu once a week, no matter where I am, and this is my regular spot for OC. Great service, top quality meat and veg, wide selection of sake and beer. Overall the best Shabu in HB and OC.
My favorite place for lunch when I'm in the area.  My teen loves it, too!
Great shabu, food, and service  You can opt for more veggie and omit tice6
Great food. Great staff. Great cleanliness. Great great great
Very helpful workers that guided me through my first shabu experience. Very nice place without great food.
This place is the best, bar none. Fresh selections, clean and fresh
As nice as usual
Coolest meal we have had in a while. Don't really know the difference in the grades of ribeye because of deli sliced we couldn't tell the flavor difference between the three.
No wait times eating late afternoon lunch. Good service, good selection.
Great service, great food, good place to hangout with friends.
Great food, quick service, and friendly staff. And they have funnel cake!
Good food, good service.. Definitely coming back.
Delicious. Delicious. Delicious. I feel like I'm family when I'm here.

Great service and wonderful food.  The quality of the meat was good, we had the prime and choice beef.  And both selections were great.  My husband got the spicy miso broth and said it probably the best he had.  That says a lot since we tried 99% of shabu establishments in the orange county area.
Really cleAn and decent food, definitely happy with my order but you need to ask for the sauce for the soup or it's too watery with the seaweed only
Fresh vegetables and high quality beef. Great service.

Not a bad place to have shabu. Only have one flavor upgrade option.  If they have a special on Kobe beef take it, it is worth it but don't know if you want to pay full price on the Kobe.  Their meat is cut very thin.   So I would fill up …

My son comes here frequently and raves about it. We came here for my wife's Birthday and had an outstanding experience from service to thr food. Ordered the Ninja portion and could only half because its sooo much!!!!! We shall return!!!
Lots of seating, remember to ask about the secret menu items.
Outstanding shabu - best hot pot I've had outside of Honolulu. My only complaint was I didn't know the ramen noodles that came in a bowl were not cooked already 🍜
awesome place, got tvs and everything. meat options are great, price is very reasonable and the soup base are great, lots of regular comes here!
Great food and service. The staff is very friendly. Literally a weekly stop for dinner.  Looking forward to their new Japanese grill.
Spicy miso broth is outstanding!
Shabu Shabu here is delicious for the price point. There's quite a variety of meats like pork and beef.  A, they have spicy drops for individuals who lack taste buds.
It was good but I've seen other shabu places with much more choices. Service was surprisingly good despite sitting in a whole separate room from the main restaurant.
Very good!
Great meat and veggie quality.  Ponzu is very good as well.  They have a good little selection of hot sauce on the bar shelf if you dare.
Amazing, just amazing...
Great food, especially the spicy miso soup! And excellent customer service. Everyone was friendly and nice and our server was terrific! We had too much food!
The food the service awesome.  Sonia is awesome highly recommend
The food is so good. So fresh.  The service is constantly friendly.  A fav for me.
Overpriced as hell. Barely get any meat for the price, and the broth options are incredibly limited (just 2 options).
Good quality meats
Good little spot!  Great meats, even their cheapest CAB does the job nicely!  Also I love their peanut dipping sauce for the meats!
So good. First time at a shabu place and it was great. Will for sure be back

Staff were friendly and were very helpful in choosing the meat. I loved the edameme as a side and also had a big variety of high quality meat. If you want low quality meat then this isnt the place to go.

Sauces puts this place just above California Shabu Shabu and it's closer to my house. Still expensive though as expected for a Japanese shabu place. Meat quality is superb and juicy. Try their Angus prime rib which is not on the menu …
Love it. The food the people and the staff. All are great. We eat here as much as we can absolutely love this place.
Very good Shabu Shabu.  Even their least expensive beef if of excellent quality.  Attentive service.

One of my favorite places to eat shabu. The broth and meat and vegetable quality are all top notch. The service is excellent and fast. The only downside I feel that this place may have is the prices are relatively high. But overall, I think that it is worth it for the quality of food.
A little on the pricey side. I would rather make it at home. Their flavors are good though.
Pretty good food, different for me but I did enjoy it. Nice scenery
Delicious food!! Clean.  Excellent service and super friendly staff. Brian is always so nice and attentive. Overall, it's a really great atmosphere super tasty food!!
Awesome food, awesome service, awesome staff.  Really enjoy the shabu here.  Their broth is rich with flavors and high quality food.  Definitely coming back.
OMG SO GOOD!!!! My new favorite shabu in town. Worth the drive from UC Irvine!!
